abstract.Desc:
This member must be implemented (or overridden) by the inheritor.
synonyms: @virtual

access.Desc: Specify the access level of this member (private, package-private, public, or protected).

alias.Desc: Treat a member as if it had a different name.

async.Desc: Indicate that a function is asynchronous.

augments.Desc:
Indicate that a symbol inherits from, and adds to, a parent symbol.
synonyms: @extends

author.Desc: Identify the author of an item.

borrows.Desc: This object uses something from another object.

class.Desc:
This function is intended to be called with the "new" keyword.
synonyms: @constructor

classdesc.Desc: Use the following text to describe the entire class.

constant.Desc:
Document an object as a constant.
synonyms: @const

constructs.Desc: This function member will be the constructor for the previous class.

createDate.Desc: Date of writing this piece of code

deprecated.Desc: Document that this is no longer the preferred way.

enum.Desc: Document a collection of related properties.

example.Desc: Provide an example of how to use a documented item.

exports.Desc: Identify the member that is exported by a JavaScript module.

external.Desc:
Identifies an external class, namespace, or module.
synonyms: @host

fires.Desc:
Describe the events this method may fire.
synonyms: @emits

function.Desc:
Describe a function or method.
synonyms: @func, @method

generator.Desc: Indicate that a function is a generator function.

hideconstructor.Desc: Indicate that the constructor should not be displayed.

ignore.Desc: Omit a symbol from the documentation.

inheritdoc.Desc: Indicate that a symbol should inherit its parent's documentation.

interface.Desc: This symbol is an interface that others can implement.

kind.Desc: What kind of symbol is this?

lends.Desc: Document properties on an object literal as if they belonged to a symbol with a given name.

license.Desc: Identify the license that applies to this code.

link.Desc:
Link to another item in the documentation.
synonyms: {@linkcode}, {@linkplain}

listens.Desc: List the events that a symbol listens for.

memberof.Desc: This symbol belongs to a parent symbol.

mixes.Desc: This object mixes in all the members from another object.

name.Desc: Document the name of an object.

override.Desc: Indicate that a symbol overrides its parent.

package.Desc: This symbol is meant to be package-private.

param.Desc:
Document the parameter to a function.
synonyms: @arg, @argument

private.Desc: This symbol is meant to be private.

property.Desc:
Document a property of an object.
synonyms: @prop

protected.Desc: This symbol is meant to be protected.

public.Desc: This symbol is meant to be public.

readonly.Desc: This symbol is meant to be read-only.

requires.Desc: This file requires a JavaScript module.

returns.Desc:
Document the return value of a function.
synonyms: @return

return.Desc: Document the return value of a function.

see.Desc: Refer to some other documentation for more information.

summary.Desc: A shorter version of the full description.

this.Desc: What does the 'this' keyword refer to here?

throws.Desc:
Describe what errors could be thrown.
synonyms: @exception

tutorial.Desc: Insert a link to an included tutorial file.

type.Desc: Document the type of an object.

variation.Desc: Distinguish different objects with the same name.

version.Desc: Documents the version number of an item.

yields.Desc:
Document the value yielded by a generator function.
synonyms: @yield
